pull_request.title: Fixed some small layout issue
pull_request.body:
The text on the info had text-white on them making them unreadable is the user doesn't have dark mode in the preferences. I've also fixed some other small layout issues:

- I've set the position of the loader to fixed and inset-0 to always cover the whole page even if the page is scrolled.
- i've added a max width to the game to fix mobile layout

issue.title: fixed #3: renamed api bindChildrens->bindChildren
issue.body: I added a deprecation warning although if the lib is not used yet and a breaking change is affordable, I would suggest to screw backwards compat and remove the deprecation altogether.

comment.body:
Childrens is wrong because it's not correct grammar.
A single element would be a child (bindChild).
You already emphasize the fact that you can pass multiple elements by calling the api bindChildren (and not bindChild).
This is the reason why also in React you have children (not childrens, not childs). See https://reactjs.org/docs/react-api.html#reactchildren

use createVariable for createComputed and createStored
Added setup function to plug a new reactivity system in Sprinkle JS

issue.title: API change 'bindChildrens' -> 'bindChildren'
issue.body:
I propose an api change for the **bindChildrens** API. I only suggest a mere renaming because of the spelling (plural of **child** is **children**, the extra **s** makes it weird and might cause some issues in the future).


Proposed change:

- Rename **bindChildrens** to **bindChildren** everywhere (code, tests, docs)
- add alias **bindChildrens** (that calls **bindChildren**) to keep backwards compatibility and avoid breaking changes

Happy to contribute to implementing this, if it is a change that is accepted.
